    public interface IFastEncodableMessage
extends IBindable<ListIterator<ITagValue>>
    Note that this is a restricted FIX centric view of what theoretically could be encoded using this FAST implementation.

    In these messages all values are associated with int tags (as is the case with FIX).

    By contrast, in FAST templates fields are identified by names and optional id's which can be general String's. For FIX, we make the id's mandatory int's, mapping to the FIX tag numbers.

    • Method Detail

      • getFieldValue

        IValue getFieldValue(int tag)
        Retrieves the value of the first tag/value field in the message with the given tag.

        Returns null or an IValue which is isNone, if no such field exists.

        the The IValue object returned by this call can be reused. Code using this method should not assume that calls for different tags return different IValue objects.

        Parameters:
        tag - Tag of field to be retrieved.
        Returns:
        Value of first field with that tag.
